Genai is pictured with her Mom, Dad, Brother and Great Grandpa.

HER WORDS:

\xe2\x80\x9cGrowing up being fourth-generation meant having to defend my family and me. Having to explain to others why we didn\xe2\x80\x99t speak Spanish or fit a certain standard of what it means to be Latinx. These experiences pushed me to grow as a person and define what it means to be Latinx from a personal standpoint. "There is no one way to be LATINX. I REPEAT NO ONE WAY! Our culture has so much diversity within itself that it is so important to celebrate, respect, and empower one another and our community's beauty and uniqueness."
